ZH: 他不应该为非作恶。
EN: He should not do evil deeds.
ZH: 做人要莫为非作恶。
EN: One should not commit evil deeds.
ZH: 不能为非作恶，要守法。
EN: Do not commit evil deeds and abide by the law.
ZH: 他们犯下了罪行，为非作恶。
EN: They committed crimes and did evil deeds.
ZH: 作为公民，我们要铭记不能为非作恶。
EN: As citizens, we must remember not to do evil deeds.
ZH: 政治家应该以身作则，绝不能为非作恶。
EN: Politicians should lead by example and never do evil deeds.
ZH: 道德准则告诉我们要远离为非作恶。
EN: Ethical guidelines tell us to stay away from doing evil deeds.
ZH: 每个人都有义务不为非作恶。
EN: Everyone has a duty not to do evil deeds.
ZH: 为非作恶只会给自己带来短暂的快感。
EN: Doing evil deeds will only bring temporary pleasure to oneself.
ZH: 严惩为非作恶的行为。
EN: Punish those who commit evil deeds.
ZH: 他的为非作恶行为被揭露了。
EN: His evil deeds were exposed.
ZH: 不能容忍为非作恶的行为。
EN: We cannot tolerate evil deeds.
ZH: 他为非作恶结果遭到了惩罚。
EN: He was punished for his evil deeds.
ZH: 勇敢地站出来，停止为非作恶的行为。
EN: Stand up bravely and stop doing evil deeds.
ZH: 政府应该采取措施惩罚为非作恶的人。
EN: The government should take measures to punish those who commit evil deeds.
ZH: 为非作恶没有好下场。
EN: There is no good outcome for those who do evil deeds.
ZH: 绝对不能为非作恶，违法者必受惩罚。
EN: Absolutely cannot do evil deeds, violators will be punished.
ZH: 我们不能纵容为非作恶的人。
EN: We cannot condone those who do evil deeds.
